  "translations": {
    "en": "al-Thaqafi. He said: al-`Abbas b. Bakkar narrated to us. He said: `Abd al-Wahid b. Abi `Amr narrated to us from al-Kalbi from Abi Salih from Abi Hurayra from the Messenger of Allah (s). He said: On the Throne, it is written: “I am Allah. There is no god but Me. I am Alone without any partners. Muhammad is My Servant and My Messenger, and I have aided him with `Ali.” So, Allah revealed, “It is He who supported you with His help and with the believers.” <a href=\"/books/quran:8#h62\">[8:62]</a> The “help” is `Ali (as), who [also] entered among the believers; so, he (as) is on both sides together.",
